What's all the fuss - haven't you other reviewers ever eaten GOOD soup. Made as directed, mostly. Had less mushrooms (about 5-6 Cups) so I only used 32oz of broth. I used about 1/2 and 1/2 crmini and fresh shiitake, since I had them on hand. Used 4 leeks for about 2-21/2 Cups after cutting. Took suggestions of previous reviewers and added sherry and 1 garlic clove. Also used my go-to seasoning, Nature's Seasoning to pump up the flavor and added small amount of Minor's chicken stock concentrate. Here's what I think. Slice the mushrooms way thinner. Saute some bacon and use the drippings to sweat the leeks in. (Not much, maybe 1 TBS instead of butter). Puree at least 1/2 the soup to concentrate the flavor and give the soup better body. The whipped cream w/ thyme was a nice touch, but it would work as well to add some cream and thyme directly to the soup and skip the whipping part. I'll make the soup again using my suggestions and re-review it. Curious to see what others think of these ideas. Very labor intensive for the result.

