This is the first review I have provided, but I loved this soup so much I wanted to share my experience and a couple of small changes that added. I think that they provided a great deal of depth to the flavor. I used 7 oz. crimini, 8 oz. white and 8 oz. shiitake...as that was what I had on hand. I had some dried Porcini and Chanterelle mushrooms in the pantry so used 1 oz of each. I reconstituted with 1.5 cups of boiling water and let soak for about 40 minutes. Drained the mushrrooms, chopped and added to the saute. Then strained the broth and used that as substitute for part of the chicken broth. Added a great earthy flavor. I used a hand held immersion blender and it was perfect for puree of the right consistency.

